ong with 1 mile and 5 mile radius approximations. As of August 2024, there were 208 WIC clinics in Washington State. Approximately 6.18 million people live within a 15 minute drive of a WIC clinic, that is 80% of the total population. Approximately 7.17 million people live within a 30 minute drive of a WIC clinic, that is 93% of the total population. Approximately 1.4 million people live within a 1 mile radius of a WIC clinic, that is 18% of the total population. Finally, approximately 6.36 million people live within a 5 mile radius of a WIC clinic, that is 83% of the total population.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":658,"renderedHeight":370,"naturalWidth":1500,"naturalHeight":1941,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 885 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":316802},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/5.0/img/logo/cdc-logo-tag-right.svg","alt":"Centers for Disease Control and Prevention","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":282,"renderedHeight":66,"naturalWidth":827,"naturalHeight":193,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":4780}]}}